{
  "text": "Deep CNN models achieve state-of-the-art performance on object detection, but are heavily dependent on largescale training data. Unfortunately, labeling images for detection is extremely time-consuming, as every instance of every object must be marked with a bounding box. Even the largest challenge datasets provide a limited number of annotated categories, e.g., 20 categories in PASCAL VOC [CITATION_1] ), 80 in COCO [CITATION_2] , and 200 in ImageNet [CITATION_3] . But what if we wanted to train a detector for a novel category? It may not be feasible to compile and annotate an extensive training set covering all possible intra-category variations.",
